summary: This document contains certified corporate records from the Delaware Division of Corporations for L.S.J. LLC, including its 1998 Certificate of Formation and a 2019 good standing certificate, provided in response to a 2019 grand jury subpoena signed by AUSA Alison Moe. It shows the FBI was investigating this corporate entity.

persons.name: Jeffrey W. Bullock
persons.context: Certifies the attached documents for L.S.J. LLC as true and correct copies from the Delaware Division of Corporations.

persons.name: Stephen B. Messinger
persons.context: The FBI document is addressed to his attention at the New York field office.

persons.name: Alison Moe
persons.context: Signed the Grand Jury Subpoena dated August 9, 2019, which requested the records for L.S.J. LLC.

persons.name: Russell R. Rosier
persons.context: Signed the Certificate of Formation for L.S.J. LLC on April 17, 1998, as the authorized person forming the LLC.

connections.description: Rosier is the authorized person who executed the Certificate of Formation for L.S.J. LLC.
Moe, as AUSA, issued the grand jury subpoena for records that were sent to the FBI's attention, likely including Messinger.

locations: Corporation Trust Center, 1209 Orange Street, Wilmington, New Castle County, Delaware 19801
keyFacts: L.S.J. LLC was formed in Delaware on April 17, 1998, with Russell R. Rosier as the authorized person.
In August 2019, a federal grand jury subpoena signed by AUSA Alison Moe requested records for L.S.J. LLC, indicating it was part of an investigation.
The Delaware Secretary of State certified on August 26, 2019, that L.S.J. LLC was in good standing and its taxes were paid to date.
The records were sent to the FBI's New York field office, attention Stephen B. Messinger.
The custodian of records declaration is partially redacted, obscuring the declarant's name and signature.
